-- Macquarie-led group to buy Louisiana utility Cleco Corp
-- By Ankush Sharma in Bangalore
-- Mon Oct 20, 2014 05:33AM EDT
-- None



Oct 20 (Reuters) - An investor group led by Macquarie Infrastructure and Real Assets has agreed to buy Louisiana electricity supplier Cleco Corp <CNL.N> in a deal valued at about $4.7 billion, including about $1.3 billion of assumed debt.

The offer price of $55.37 per share represents a premium of about 15 percent to Cleco's close on Friday. [ID:nHUGchbwpr]